  "thirdPlaceNote": "After the group stage, the third-placed teams of all 12 groups are ranked against each other by: (1) points, (2) goal difference, (3) goals scored, (4) fair play (disciplinary) points, then (5) drawing of lots. The top 8 of these 12 advance to the Round of 32. Eight R32 slots are reserved for them (matches 74, 77, 79, 80, 81, 82, 85, 87), and each slot has a published list of 5 candidate groups (e.g. match 74's opponent must be the third-placed team from group A, B, C, D or F). FIFA assigns the 8 qualified third-placed teams to slots using an official allocation table keyed on the exact combination of 8 groups that produced qualifiers: every team is placed into a slot whose candidate-group list contains its group, each slot receives exactly one team, and no third-placed team can face the winner of its own group (the candidate lists already exclude the slot's group-winner's group). To implement: take the 8 qualifying group letters, then find the unique (per FIFA's table) perfect matching between those letters and the 8 slots subject to each slot's candidate list — a bipartite matching over the candidate lists reproduces the official assignment; if multiple matchings exist, follow FIFA's published combination table, which resolves ties deterministically."
